<p style="text-align: center">
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->TRANSCRIPT OF INTERVIEW OF SEN. SERGE OSME&Ntilde;A 10 June 2014 <!-- NewsTitle.end --></span>
</p>
<!-- NewsBody.start -->
<p style="text-align: justify">On the confirmation of DENR Sec. Paje</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Malabo pa rin po bang ma-confirm si Sec. Paje?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Hindi, mako-confirm na siya. Outvoted na ako eh, buo 'yung House (of Representatives) eh. Ako lang mag-isa.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Natuwa na po ba kayo sa mga sagot niya?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Hindi, there were a lot of contradictions. But you know, it's already the end of sessions here, tapusin na natin ito, and the congressmen wanted to vote on it, and I didn't get a single vote. Para akong lone ranger.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: In a nutshell, bakit po para sa inyo hindi siya dapat ma-confirm sa CA as DENR Secretary?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Well, there are many issues. And it's mostly nahihirapan siyang mag-prevent, you know naman, matagal na itong mga kalokohang ito -- mga illegal mining, black sand minding, illegal quarrying, etc. That's my opinion.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Okay lang kayo na nakalusot sa inyo?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Wala akong magagawa. They want to vote on it, and I don't want to block the right to vote.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Are you disappointed?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: YES! Disappointed. But now, I can rest. ?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Will you invoke Section 20 in the plenary?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: I have never invoked Section 20 in my 15 years in the Senate. But I am not saying I will not.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Bakit po (pinabayaan niyong mawala na?)</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: You ask the congressmen. Why? Because that's the decision of  the House panel.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: May package deal na ba?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: No comment. Laughs ?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Consequence ng confirmation ni Paje?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Id on't know Marami naman kine-question diyan sa Gabinete ni PNOY who lack the competence but they still back them up. Wala naman tayong magagawa, that's the prerogative of he president. It's a pity for the country, but what can we do?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Same thing with Petilla?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: I will not answer that question, let's cross the bridge when we get there.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">*****</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Ano pong nangyari? Napagod na po kayo?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Yeah. It's tiring to study. Kahapon, mga 3 hours. Last week din.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Pinagbigyan mo na lang?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: No. Hindi ko pinagbigyan. I told them I will vote 'No' but the congressmen said they will vote as a bloc, they will all vote in favor. Talo ako.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Hindi ka talaga kumbinsido?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: if you listen, if you read the Transcripts, you'll know why.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sa plenary, hindi mo na i-o-oppose> ?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: If I am able to attend the plenary tomorrow, I will vote 'No'. I have to be consistent.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: I told them, tutal out-numbered naman ako, bukas na lang ako mag-e-explain ng vote para nasa records.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Did they appeal to you?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: No, no, they did not. They let me talk, as long as I want. They asked me pa nga, you need  another 6 hours, go ahead and we will just sit here. But we will vote.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Anong sinasabi nila sayo?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: They were joking. Alam ko naman kung ano ang takbo ng Commission on Appointments. I know that the House votes as a bloc I know that the House gets the marching orders, and they will vote that way. And they told me, 'Pare sorry.' Nag-sorry naman sila lahat.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: So may marching order to confirm Paje? But they let you talk?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Yes. They know eventually I'll get tired.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q:  Tomorrow you will explain in the Senate floor?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Yes.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">On Sen. Revilla's Privileged Speech</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Ano pong masasabi niyo sa Privileged Speech kahapon ni Sen. Bong?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Ang galing kumanta,  hindi ba?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Nakakuha kaya sya ng simpatiya ng public?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Siyempre naman. It was an emotional speech, para siyang nagfe-farewell na sa Senado. Binigay naman niya 'yung layuning niya, and yeah, it was clearly emotional for a lot of his people  who voted for him. It's sad. It's sad.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">On the 3 senators in Napolist</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: They have said they are willing and ready to go to jail. Ano ang implication sa Senate kung makulong sila?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Ang implikasyon sa Senado? Wala po naman. Okay lang. we will have to continue, mas dadami ang trabaho natin. Pero, we have to continue.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sabi ni Sen. Revilla kahapon. Huwag naman gamitin ang CA?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Hindi po  totoo iyan.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: 'Yun na daw ang legacy diyan, kaya timing sa pagbukas ng Kongreso?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Hindi po totoo iyan, I will take issue with that. Hindi naman po Palasyo ang magpo-prosecute. It was the COA that exposed this. Atsaka itong COA, nag-umpisa ito sa COA ni Gloria, 2009. Lumabas ang mga ito. So, paano naging kasalanan n PNOY 'yun?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Under our system, it is the Department of Justice that investigates and then it hands it over to the Ombudsman, and then the Sandiganbayan. Malaca&ntilde;ang has nothing to do with it.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Gamitin para dun sa design to abolish Congress?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: That's too far-fetched.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: What's the value of Sen. Revilla's speech? How did you find it?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: I haven't really thought about it. Pero siyempre naman, in a situation like this, you'd like to give your side. And he gave his side. So, it's helpful to him.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: 'Yung pagpapaalam niya pansamantala, confirmation ba iyon? Nag-give up na siya na inevitable na ang arrest niya?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: That was emotional. Hindi ko alam kung inevitable ha.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Heart-tugging.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Ma-appreciate ba 'yun ng public?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Alam niyo, maawain ang mga Pilipino eh. So of course, that will be effective.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Naawa din kayo?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Serge: Siyempre, naawa din ako. Kaibigan ko siya eh.</p>
